\f1\u-10179?\u-8480?\u-497?\f2  \f0 Implementation Plan\par
1. Authentication (Google OAuth 2.0)\par
You will use Google Sign-In for friction-free registration. However, Google's OAuth policies strictly prohibit passing adult-oriented scopes or displaying explicit content during the Google authentication flow.\par
\par
The Flow: The user authenticates via Google. Your backend receives the Google ID token, extracts the email and basic profile, and creates a "Pending Verification" account flag.\par
\par
The Rule: You cannot use Google's basic profile to legally guarantee the user is 18+ for adult content compliance; you must gate the app behind your ID verification step right after they log in for the first time.\par
\par
2. Age & National ID Verification (eKYC)\par
Connecting directly to the Philippine government\f2\rquote\f0 s PhilSys / eGovPH database for private commercial apps is restricted. Instead, you must integrate a certified third-party eKYC provider operating in the Philippines (such as Sumsub, Smile Identity, or Zignsec).\par
\par
The Technical Flow:\par
\par
The frontend initiates a verification session via your backend to the eKYC API.\par
\par
The eKYC Web SDK opens a secure camera widget for the user.\par
\par
The user takes a photo of their Philippine National ID (PhilID / ePhilID) and a live selfie (Liveness Check to prevent fraud/photos of photos).\par
\par
The provider's AI runs OCR (Optical Character Recognition) on the ID to extract the Date of Birth and calculates if the age is greater than or equal to 18.\par
\par
The provider sends a secure webhook back to your server with the status (APPROVED or REJECTED).\par
\par
Here is a typical backend implementation processing that webhook:\par
\par
JavaScript\par
// Example Node.js Express Webhook for eKYC status updates\par
app.post('/api/v1/kyc/webhook', async (req, res) => \{\par
    const signature = req.headers['x-kyc-signature'];\par
    \par
    // 1. Verify webhook signature for security\par
    if (!verifyWebhookSource(req.body, signature)) \{\par
        return res.status(401).send('Unauthorized Source');\par
    \}\par
\par
    const \{ userId, status, verificationData \} = req.body;\par
\par
    if (status === 'COMPLETED' && verificationData.isOver18) \{\par
        // 2. Update user status in your Database (e.g., PostgreSQL)\par
        await db.user.update(\{\par
            where: \{ id: userId \},\par
            data: \{ \par
                isVerifiedAdult: true,\par
                kycReference: verificationData.idNumberHash // Hash for privacy compliance\par
            \}\par
        \});\par
        return res.status(200).send('User Verified');\par
    \}\par
\par
    return res.status(400).send('Verification Failed or Underage');\par
\});\par
